'''Reg Morrison''' (14 September 1932 – 2006) was a Scottish professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].

==Career==
Born in [[Gourdon, Aberdeenshire|Gourdon]], Morrison played for [[Lewis United F.C.|Lewis United]], [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]], [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]], [[Stirling Albion F.C.|Stirling Albion]] and [[Deveronvale F.C.|Deveronvale]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player9/regmorrison.html|title=Profile|accessdate=30 April 2014|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://backoffice.afc.co.uk/Team/CurrentSquad/player_show.cfm?player_id=571&Season=1958-59|title=Profile|accessdate=30 April 2014|publisher=Aberdeen F.C. Heritage Trust}}</ref>

